        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Hey.</P><P>The scariest thing for me in this petition thread, was the suggestion that it be locked, against the posibility, that anyone would dare to disagree.  This is all the more surreal, when it was a druid that was disagreeing.  <i>(You could make a strong argument that if it were, say a necromancer, making remarks like, "I hate Druids. Over powered as it is and yet they still ask to be even more group friendly," that this was just a cross class issue.)</i><BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>The scariest thing is that you’re not understand what it is Druids are asking for.  I wasn’t exaggerating what they are asking for. I explained it in fair easy to understand terms.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>I don't play a druid and I don't group enough to go criticising which classes are, or aren't balanced, really.  <i>(I do carry the standard annoyance at trying to hunt something, only to find that a druid is hogging all the spawns, but what can ya do?  (I'm compensated for this by watching quad kiters get ripped to shreds, every so often, when they run outta mana.))</i>  And, I only tend to browse other classes forums, on occaisions such as this, where a link is posted.  However, I have noticed that almost invariably, the link is always accompanied by derision of whatever class it is who feel the need improving.  The general response here seems to be almost that druids deserve to beaten soundly with the nerf bat, rather than improved in any way.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Well, excuse the fuck out-a-me.  You might call my explanation a criticism but I’ll call it an explanation, thank you very much.  </P><P>The Druid petition isn’t just about improving their already immensely sought after class, their petition is about making the Druid class essential as the secondary healer on large raids and their little “improvement” would make the Druid class capable of EXCLUDING Clerics on smaller raids.  </P><P>I certainly wasn’t calling for a nerf or Druids, I was providing support for the “suffering” Druids were complaining about enduring and the reason for the petition.  </P><P><BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></P><P>The curiousity in this, is that I'm fairly sure that if I was to hunt around a bit, I could probably find the occaisional thread on other classes boards, that does the same thing.  <i>(Posts linking to here, so everyone can deride what the 'stupid necros' want.  Posts linking to mage boards, so people can laugh that mages think their pet is underpowered.  You know what I mean.)</i>  This can't possibly help anyone.  All that this leads to is that no-one gets anything.  <i>(Druids get nothing, 'cos we have announce they need whupping with the nerf bat.  Necros get nothing, 'cos druids announced that we need an equally sound whupping with the bat.  Mages get nothing, 'cos everyone has pet envy.  And so on.)</i><BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>All “stupid” necromancers want is a legitimate purpose and role post 53. Find me one of those “let’s laugh at the necromancers” threads on another board.  I’ll enjoy reading it.  </P><P>Why do you think this can’t help anyone?  I’d think that developers not wasting time on flippant whines and focusing on genuine concerns would be a benefit for everyone not a hindrance.  You realize those “Druids” sent that petition to Verant, you realize those Druids are serious?  Those individuals actually believe they have a legitimate concern.  They don’t and some times people need a dose of reality.  Druids’ certainly do.  </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>After all, this <b>is</b> how nerfs happen.  You remember Mrylokar's dagger?  It didn't get nerfed 'cos the guy who got it stanted sending tells to GMs explaining it was too powerful.  It was nerfed, because a million and one people, who saw it on sites like Allakhazam's, starting bitching about it.  <i>(I find it extremely hard to believe that Verant's QA group did this off their own back, because if that was the case, it'd have been 'fixed', before it went live!)</i><BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Verant has always relied on the stupidity of its’ customers when it comes to item nerfs.  Class nerfs come from misconceptions and preconceived notions most of the time.  </P><P>I hate Druids.  I kill ‘em all the time, every chance I get.  Sue me.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>I know full well that it's not gonna happen, but I genuinely believe that we'd get a whole lot further, if everyone wasn't busy tryin' to shout everyone else down.  <BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I'm not posting on the Druid boards, what's your point?</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>I'm also inclined to believe that no druid really expects to get the whole of their list of requests.  <i>(Well, some of them no doubt do, but there's never a shortage of idiots, playing any class.)</i><BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>You’re foolish as Hell then.  That petition was written as a reasonable request.  The creator of that petition considers the requests a reasonable solution to the problem.  Or didn’t you read the thread?  Are you saying the writer of the petition is an idiot?</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>  A round of balancing is coming up and it's like a kid's Christmas list.  This is the list of presents they want.  If they get a coupla things, no doubt they'll be happy.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>That is what angers me so much, that attitude you’re displaying, its defeatist.  It really is.  How can anyone who is reasonable even consider giving Druids yet another improvement?  For the love of Inny are you insane?  It would be nice if just once a Necromancer had more value than a Druid in a group, just one time…  </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Curiously, everyone seems to have missed the root of this petition.  At the very base of the issue, is the argument, "Norrath has gotten tougher and we haven't!"  This is the same problem necromancers are bitching about.  <i>(And, though I don't know it for sure, I'd be willing to gamble, the same problem as everyone else who currently feels underpowered.)</i><BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>No you’ve missed the root of the petition, completely.  I suggest you re-read it.  The petition is unreasonable, and written based on the abilities of other classes and uses the abilities of other classes to justify improvement to the Druid class.  </P><P>Necromancers don’t feel under powered.  We feel useless.  There’s a pretty big difference between our concerns and the Druid concerns.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR><i>"Druids whining for enhancements is a frigging joke on a monumental scale."</i><BR>How many boards do you suppose I could find the same remark on, but directed at necromancers?<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>None. Show me one.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Anyhow.  I can't see this being a popular line of thought.  Added to which, I'm bored and the servers should be comin' up soon...</P><P>*Shrug*</P><P>AlAaraaf.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote><BR>It couldn’t possibly be a popular line of thought, as it contains no thought whatsoever.  <BR>I disagree with the entire philosophy of love they neighbor.  I’m a necromancer, not some tree hugging, quad kiting, Root DoTing, six-man raid essential class that only wants to be the equivalent of a non-soloing class in ability.</P><P><BR><img src="http://www.gibnet.gi/~rondu/necromancer.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
