        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I would tend to agree with those remarking that Druids are an easy class to play. I've found my Druid--currently 26 on Brell--somewhat boring to work with. Stand, heal, nuke, sit. /yawn. Playing a Druid can not only be boring as all hell,  but also annoying if you are like my Druid, and refuse to be a buff whore. In fact, the only thing that continues to retain my interest in the roleplay aspect--I play a Half Elf Druid who hates Tunare.</P><P>So, I started a Iksar Necromancer named Arkaron--also on Brell, say hi!--and was thrilled by how fun this class is to play. I actually get to think...</P><P>Druid/Necro issues seem to be very different. Druids want extras, I think. Necros just want to be Necros...</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
