nyone else other than the tanks! A druid should be nuking or healing! Snaring even! Not meleeing! A druid can't melee for shit!</P><P>I will admit I was pissed off at the amount of druid bashing going on. Hell, whenever I play my other classes I curse at the kiting druids all the time...<BR>But the petition is sincere. That necros and mages are also broken? I admit that too, but that is something YOU have to deal with, don't expect another class to know yours as good as you, and vice versa. I group regularly with necros and mages in my guild, and we don't have such a bad time.<BR>I am still VERY pissed off at the amount of people who have NO idea at a druid's role in the end game. That is why the Druid petition was created. We don't wanna be uber, shit, I've NEVER even felt uber at being a druid. I feel more uber with my wurmy wielding warrior at level 27 than I feel as my druid at 55. I go invis in newbie zones just to not attract attention, and I ALWAYS help people out. If I can't I apologise 'sorry, real busy atm' and even go WAY out of my way to try and help them later. That is the kind of person I am, and I happen to play a druid...<BR>Last night, in ME, was grouped with some guildies. A 53 enchanter runs past and asks me for SoE. I Give it to her. 3 minutes later I see she has mezzed a mob (those primitive looking Gatherers and Followers...) and is attacking another with it. Mez drops, they both charge her. Her health drops like a bomb, but I manage to cast Chloroblast and save her just as she runs a short distance and mezzes again... That is the kind of character I play. And being a Druid allows me to do it.</P><P>You don't think our petition is fair?<BR>Laugh when Verant rejects it.<BR>Or<BR>Learn when they make changes to adjust the situation.</P><P>If you guys feel broken, make a petition. Caster balancing is just around the corner.</P><P>Ciao for now!</P><P>Araxx Darkroot - 55 Preserver<BR>Clan of the Roc<BR>Bristlebane</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="ico