        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hi Araxx....<BR> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>when I feel like playing a class that only has to fear and dot and sic his pet on the running mob, and doesn't want a ton of tells asking to be buffed, sowed, ported, etc, then I play my necro <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Geez maybe I should start a Druid - at least that way ppl might actually ???need??? something from me..... (get the idea? druids are needed in the game.... necros are not) As it is now I get a request from somone I don't know from a bar of soap perhaps once every two weeks for a corpse summons - and I ALWAYS drop whatever I am doing unless it is a raid to do it for them.</P><P>Regarding the crappy fear raids I've been on... Yes you are completely correct. Fear Raids pretty much are crappy, they are done at levels where people have very little experience working with raid force strengths. I once again however stick to what I said - sit down to med in fear when a mob is engaged or mob's are mezzed and you almost guarantee you get aggro. I know this from my own personal experience as "my role is to make mana and pump" so I get aggro there a lot.</P><P>This brings me to a minor rant. Fear is the perfect zone for pet classes (that know how to control their pets) to contribute. Yet I've only been on a single fear raid (out of about 30) where the raid leader had the balls to tell the numerous idiots to shut the fuck up as pets were fine. Damnit even in closed guild raids I've been denied the use of my pet in fear. The worst thing about this is that this is where ppl "learn" that pets and dots are **BAD IN RAIDS**, sadly most players are so clueless about pet classes that they just accept this nonsense as fact. Why? becuase there are so few high level pet class players in the game that they never get first hand experience with them - WE ARE DIEING OUT. Druids are not dieing out by any stretch of the imagination.</P><P>I'm through bashing you Araxx and I repeat again - I don't bash Druids - but I most certainly stick to my guns on bashing their over the top petition.</P><P>Regarding petitioning VI, I have subitted dozens of requests to them on their censored message boards. All that I have received back from them is their boilerplate responses. I'm done with that :(. Or do you like engaging in long distance conversations with someone who does not talk back at all apart from answering the phone with the message "Thank you for calling about whatever you are calling about"?</P><P>Much better to post on a forum like this where people respond to your ideas and point out what is wrong with them than to submit them to VI's black hole of a message board. If VI don't read this forum, and the other forums for the other classes then they are truly stupid. Heck I've even given them the URL to this forum - never got a reply but I told the VI black hole all about it's great ideas.</P><P>Read thru all the posts I have made on this board and I sincerely doubt you will find me bashing any class. Bashing VI or individuals sure (hehe you come to mind....) but I never tolerate bashing classes and shout out whenever I see it. Some ppl on this board do directly bash druids but their rants are so over the top they need to be taken with a pinch of salt.</P><P>Why am I and so many other necro's frustrated? Becuase to get a necro or any other character to well past level 50 you have to put in a huge investment in time. To finally get near the pinnacle of your class and gradually come to the realization that you have made a huge error in class choice becuase VI have destroyed your class and made you worthless is pretty damn frustrating.</P><P>Druids cannot claim that they are worthless at all they are valued members of raids for the simple fact that they are jack of all trades, sure they can't CHEAL but the number of things they can do is nothing short of amazing.</P><P>I don't play a druid, never have and never will - the class for some reason has absolutely no attraction for me (that is not a bash just a plain fact). However let me run down the list of things that I know from experience druids can contribute to an ongoing raid....</P><P>1/ Buffs, they have a huge range of ESSENTIAL buffs (circles, POTG? regen's, SOW, SOE etc etc etc.)<BR>2/ Lull type spells, they can calm mobs that might add.<BR>3/ Heals, might not be the best but if the MA is doing their job they are more than adequate.<BR>4/ DD, they have a wide range of DD that actually stick to mobs.<BR>5/ Snare, they can no-summons pull or snare mobs already engaged.<BR>6/ Track, they can keep watch and monitor for potential adds.<BR>7/ Debuff, they have quite a wide range of mob debuff abilities.<BR>8/ DoT, might not be the best but they have them.</P><P>These abilities make druids very sought after in the high end game.</P><P>Now the druids can not only do these things but they are actively encouraged to do so during raid level events.</P><P>What are necros relegated to doing at high level raids? I don't have to say it as everyone knows but I will anyway. Pump Mana. Period. Is that an essential ability? NOPE. In fact just adding another cleric eliminates and more than replaces the necro.</P><P>The real problem with druids is that there are simply sooooo many of them that a lot have real trouble getting into high end guilds.</P><P>I sincerely believe that last statement. If I was Verant I would seriously consider reducing their functionality to try and reduce their numbers to manageable levels.</P><P>But what I truly hope for is not that druids get nerfed. No way in hell should they get ANY of the things they are whining about before the BROKEN classes are fixed though!!!! No what I hope is that the broken classes are actually fixed and reintroduced into the high end game.</P><P></P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
